b'"He could have just handed us the coloring book Target was offering for Dr. Seuss\xe2\x80\x99 birthday. He could have quickly silenced my kid with the free fruit snacks offered. You didn\xe2\x80\x99t just read my son a book. You made a difference. b'Avocado Toast Salad? Yes, please. :avocado: Try this fresh & tasty salad for a simple weeknight meal from #GoodAndGather. :green_salad: #Tastemade

Avocado Rose Salad

Ingredients:
1 Good and Gather avocado toast chopped salad kit
1/2 ripe avocado
1 grilled chicken breast

Steps:
1. Prepare the Good and Gather avocado toast chopped salad kit according to the package directions.
2. Lay the avocado cut side down, and slice it thinly crosswise.
3. Fan the avocado slices so they form a long line with the slices overlapping each other. Starting from one end, curl the avocado slices toward the center until you get a rose.
4. Squeeze some lemon juice on the rose to keep it looking fresh, and carefully place it into the center of the salad.
5. Slice the grilled chicken breast into strips and fan it out round the rose. Enjoy!'

b'"Thank you Target! :direct_hit::grinning_face::clapping_hands: Today Oliver stopped me dead in his tracks and turned back around to see this picture that he spotted! He just stared at it in awe! I am so happy that other kids that pass through here with their parents, will see this! There is a lot of focus on representing diversity, but representing people with disabilities is just as important! :red_heart:" - Thanks for sharing your story Ollie! It\'s moments like this that inspire us to do what we do. :camera: FB: Ollie\'s World'

b"Have you tried oat milk yet? Watch for new ways to use this non-dairy milk that don't involve your morning coffee. :hot_beverage:

Blueberry Chia Pudding

Ingredients:
2 cups Pacific Oat Milk
1 cup frozen blueberries
1 teaspoon vanilla
\xc2\xbd tablespoon maple syrup
\xc2\xbd cup chia seeds
\xc2\xbd cup fresh blueberries, frozen

Steps:
1. Combine Pacific Oat Milk, blueberries, vanilla and maple syrup in a blender. Stir in chia seeds and pour into jars. Refrigerate for one hour or up to overnight. Top with blueberries and and serve.

b"Mix up girls' night with this Strawberry Mango Margarita Mocktail! :strawberry::mango: Shop #GoodAndGather Strawberry Mango Sparkling Water via link in bio. 
Recipe: 
Ingredients
1/4 cup \xe2\x80\x8bsparkling or granulated sugar 
1 teaspoon kosher salt
1 teaspoon lime zest
2 cups frozen mango
1/4 cup agave nectar
1/2 cup Good & Gather Strawberry Mango Sparkling Water
1/3 cup fresh squeezed lime juice
2 cups frozen strawberries
Lime wedge for garnish

Steps
1. In a shallow bowl, combine sparkling sugar, salt and lime zest. Set aside.
2. Next, add the frozen mango to a blender along with half of the agave, half the sparkling water and half of the lime juice. Blend on high for about 3 minutes until smooth and creamy. 3. Pour mixture into pitcher and rinse the blender.
4. Next, add the frozen strawberries to the clean blender along with the rest of the agave, sparkling water and lime juice. Repeat the blending process until smooth and creamy, about 3 minutes.
5. Using a lime wedge, moisten the rim of 4 margarita glasses.
6. Dip the rim of each glass into the sugar, salt and lime zest mixture, shaking off any excess.
7. Alternate the mango and strawberry slushies into the rimmed glasses using a large spoon for an extra impressive layered look. Serve each mocktail with a lime wedge and enjoy immediately."

b"We're going coco-nuts for #GoodAndGather Coconut Chips! :coconut: Try this delicious recipe:

Good & Gather Coconut Almond Brittle

Ingredients\xe2\x81\xa0:
2 cups sugar\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x85\x93 cup corn syrup\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x85\x94 cups water \xe2\x81\xa0
\xc2\xbd teaspoon salt\xe2\x81\xa0
2 tablespoons butter\xe2\x81\xa0
1 cup Good & Gather Coconut Chips\xe2\x81\xa0
\xc2\xbd cup whole almonds\xe2\x81\xa0
1 teaspoon vanilla\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x81\xa0
Steps\xe2\x81\xa0:
1. Prepare a half baking sheet with a silicone baking mat and set aside. Combine sugar, corn syrup, and water in a large saucepan. \xe2\x81\xa0
2. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Once dissolved, cook without touching or stirring until temperature reaches 265 degrees. Add salt and butter and cook further to 300 degrees. \xe2\x81\xa0
3. Pour sugar mixture onto prepared baking sheet and sprinkle Good & Gather Coconut Chips and almonds evenly across the pan. \xe2\x81\xa0
4. Allow to cool completely for up to one hour. Break up into desired pieces and serve."
